      "text": "Ah.\n\nIronically also true for different reasons.\n\nOn Windows, ls becomes an alias to Get-ChildItem.  But since it has different parameters than the Unix ls command this can annoy people.\n\nFor that reason, on Linux / MacOS, ls is not an alias.\n\n🤷 Can always `Remove-Alias ls` 🤷"
